WEBVTT

00:02.170 --> 00:09.500
What's one of the coolest features native apps can access and can use? Push notifications,

00:09.540 --> 00:14.000
there's no better way of getting your users back into your application.

00:14.020 --> 00:17.780
You have your mobile phone in your pocket and suddenly it vibrates,

00:17.890 --> 00:22.990
you have a look at it and you see there is this new article you definitely have to read in your favorite

00:22.990 --> 00:23.610
app,

00:23.920 --> 00:30.110
well you just tap on the notification and boom, you're on the article. From a developer perspective,

00:30.130 --> 00:31.010
that's awesome,

00:31.090 --> 00:36.530
that's the best way to drive user engagement and re-engage users with your application.

00:36.580 --> 00:42.430
And from a user perspective, you get informed about things which matter to you, at least if it's done

00:42.520 --> 00:43.810
in a good way.

00:44.140 --> 00:49.080
In this module, you will learn how you can enable push notifications in web apps.

00:49.210 --> 00:55.890
Yes, this is possible and this will also, at least for Android, even work if your phone is in your pocket.

00:56.140 --> 01:02.110
Let's see how we enable push notifications and how we add such a feature to our application.
